    ğŸ”¹ `--unixsocket=FILENAME` --> ğŸ›¤ï¸ Use a UNIX domain socket instead of a TCP socket.
    ğŸ”¹ `--display=DISPLAY` --> ğŸ–¥ï¸ Specifies the DISPLAY that `broadwayd` should connect to. If not specified, the DISPLAY is taken from the `DISPLAY` environment variable.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ gtk4-broadwayd --port=8080

    ğŸ”¹ Runs broadwayd on port 8080. You can then connect to the GTK application in a browser at address `http://localhost:8080`.

    $ gtk4-broadwayd --address=192.168.1.100

    ğŸ”¹ Runs broadwayd on address 192.168.1.100.

